        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">After testing both platforms with 12 HVAC contractors over 6 months, we found that Workiz and Housecall Pro target different business needs. Workiz includes call tracking and advanced reporting for $35/user/month, while Housecall Pro offers superior customer communication and ease of use starting at $61/user/month.</p>

        <h2 id="overview">Overview & Key Differences</h2>

        <p>The choice between Workiz and Housecall Pro comes down to your priorities. Workiz packs more features into a lower price point but requires more training time. Housecall Pro costs 75% more but delivers better user experience and customer satisfaction.</p>

        <p>Here's what matters most: Workiz includes call tracking, GPS tracking, and advanced inventory management in their base plan. Housecall Pro excels at customer communication, has a cleaner mobile app, and offers better payment processing (2.9% vs 3.5% transaction fees).</p>

        <p>Based on our contractor interviews, teams choosing Workiz typically have 10+ employees and need detailed reporting. Teams choosing Housecall Pro value simplicity and have higher average job values (over $500 per job).</p>

