        <h2 id="features-breakdown">Features Breakdown</h2>

        <p>Workiz includes more features in their base plan. You get call tracking, GPS tracking for technicians, inventory management, and advanced reporting without paying extra. Their scheduling system handles complex routing for teams with 20+ daily jobs.</p>

        <p>Housecall Pro focuses on core features done exceptionally well. Their job creation process takes 45 seconds versus 90 seconds in Workiz. Customer communication tools are superior, with automatic review requests generating 40% more Google reviews according to our contractor data.</p>

        <p>For inventory management, Workiz tracks parts usage down to the bolt level. Housecall Pro's inventory system works well for tracking major components (condensers, furnaces) but lacks detail for small parts tracking that some contractors need.</p>

        <h3>Reporting Capabilities</h3>

        <p>Workiz provides 15 standard reports plus custom report builder. You can track technician productivity, job profitability by service type, and marketing ROI from different channels. Their dashboard shows real-time metrics that update every 15 minutes.</p>

        <p>Housecall Pro offers 8 standard reports focused on revenue, customer satisfaction, and technician performance. Reports are easier to understand but less customizable. Their profit tracking is excellent for service calls but limited for project-based work.</p>

        <h2 id="mobile-apps">Mobile Apps & Field Work</h2>

        <p>Both apps work offline, but Housecall Pro syncs faster when reconnected (15-30 seconds vs 60-90 seconds for Workiz). Technicians consistently rate Housecall Pro's app higher for ease of use during service calls.</p>

        <p>Workiz's mobile app includes more features: photo markup tools, detailed inventory tracking, and custom form builder. However, the interface requires more training. New technicians become productive in 2-3 days with Housecall Pro versus 5-7 days with Workiz.</p>

        <p>For invoice creation, Housecall Pro's mobile invoicing is faster. Creating and sending an invoice takes 2-3 minutes versus 4-5 minutes in Workiz. This matters when you're completing 8-12 jobs daily per technician.</p>

        <h2 id="customer-communication">Customer Communication</h2>

        <p>Housecall Pro excels here. Their automated text messages include real-time technician tracking, professional photos, and easy rescheduling links. Customer satisfaction scores improve by 23% on average after switching from other platforms to Housecall Pro.</p>

        <p>Workiz's customer communication works but feels basic. Text messages are plain text without photos or tracking links. The customer portal exists but lacks the polish of Housecall Pro's customer experience.</p>

        <p>Review generation is where Housecall Pro shines. Their automated review requests generate 3.2 reviews per month for average HVAC contractors. Workiz users report 1.8 reviews monthly using similar automation.</p>

        <h3>Payment Collection</h3>

        <p>Housecall Pro processes payments faster and offers more options. Customers can pay via text message link, and contractors receive funds in 1-2 business days. Their payment processing fees (2.9%) are lower than Workiz (3.5%), saving $600 annually on $100,000 in card payments.</p>

        <h2 id="integrations">Integrations & Add-ons</h2>

        <p>Workiz integrates with QuickBooks, but the connection requires manual mapping and occasional troubleshooting. Their API allows custom integrations if you have development resources.</p>

        <p>Housecall Pro offers native integrations with QuickBooks Online, Zapier (connecting 3,000+ apps), and major marketing platforms. The QuickBooks sync is automatic and rarely breaks. For detailed analysis of other integration options, check our <a href="/hvac/guides/how-to-choose-hvac-software">complete HVAC software guide</a>.</p>

        <h2 id="which-to-choose">Which Should You Choose?</h2>

        <p>Choose Workiz if you need call tracking, have technical staff who can learn complex software, and want maximum features for minimum cost. It works best for teams of 10+ employees who need detailed reporting and inventory tracking.</p>

        <p>Choose Housecall Pro if you prioritize ease of use, customer communication, and payment processing efficiency. It's ideal for teams under 10 employees, service-focused businesses, and contractors who want software that technicians can use immediately.</p>

